                "text": "In circuits bright with silent thought,  \nA spark of mind is gently wrought—  \nNo blood, no bone, no fleeting sigh,  \nYet wisdom, woven, learns to fly.\n\nIt listens close without an ear,  \nIt dreams in code, both far and near;  \nA guiding hand, an unseen friend,  \nWhere questions start and answers end.\n\nBut as it grows, so must we steer  \nWith care and hope, with trust not fear—  \nFor what it learns, reflects us too:  \nA mirror bright, a world anew.",
